page.title: 20LOCAL WILDLIFE
page.content: The extensive mudflats and farmland to the south of the{West End of {Clevedon}provide the habitat for a wide variety of plants and animals. {Plants. Sea lavender,cowslip,herb Robert,white beam,primrose,sea pink,crow garlic, lady's bed straw,bird's foot trefoil. {Birds. Redshank,curlew,dunlin,stonechat,black headed gull,herring gull,lapwing, snipe,ringed plover,little stint, shell duck,mallard,swan,sparrow hawk, peregrine falcon,little owl,long tailed tits,rooks,wheatears,house martins,skylarks,swallows,grey heron, swift,ring ouzel,robin. {Sea life. Eels,jelly fish,crabs,cuttle fish,winkles etc. {Land animals. Badgers,otters,foxes.
